Eugenia Umińska (4 October 1910, Warsaw – 20 November 1980, Kraków) was a Polish violinist.
From 1915 to 1918, she was a member of the Warsaw Music Society, where she was a student of  Mieczysław Michałowicz.
From 1919 till 1927 she studied at the Warsaw Conservatory with Józef Jarzębski.
